HEADWORD: Damiana
<hw>Da`mi*a"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.; of uncertain
origin.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A Mexican drug, used as an
aphrodisiac.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ There are several varieties derived from different
plants, esp. from a species of <gen>Turnera</gen> and from
<spn>Bigelovia veneta</spn>. <rj><au>Wood & Bache.</au></rj> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Damianist</ent>⟦br⟧
